			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">TLSROM uses the bit that would have let you have 256 KiB (instead of 128KiB) of CHR to instead control mirroring.<br /><br />As tepples is fond of pointing out, a game <em>could</em> have suffered through having these bits control both the MSB of CHR bank as well as CIRAM A10. If you want to modify an existing board to do this, it's easy: what would be CHR A17 is currently CIRAM A10. Just connect it also.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
